sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as maas-default-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS Terminate
    participant Authorino as Kuadrant/Authorino<br/>gRPC ext_authz
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Limitador as Kuadrant/Limitador<br/>gRPC mTLS
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP TLS
    participant ModelPod as LLMInferenceService<br/>Model Backend

    Note over Client,ModelPod: Flow 1: API Key Validation (Model Inference Request)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/{model}:predict<br/>Auth: Bearer sk-oai-*<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS Terminate
    Gateway->>Authorino: ext_authz check<br/>gRPC mTLS (Istio)
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+
    MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: Validate key hash<br/>5432/TCP TLS Password
    PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Key valid + user identity + groups
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: 200 OK (user, groups)
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /v1/subscriptions/select<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Selected subscription + tier
    Authorino->>Limitador: Token rate limit check<br/>gRPC mTLS (Istio)
    Limitador-->>Authorino: Rate limit OK
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth OK + metadata
    Gateway->>ModelPod: Forward request<br/>X-MaaS-Username/Group headers
    ModelPod-->>Gateway: Inference response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over Client,PostgreSQL: Flow 2: API Key Management

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>Auth: Bearer sk-oai-* or OC token<br/>HTTPS/443
    Gateway->>Authorino: ext_authz check<br/>gRPC mTLS
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: Validate auth<br/>HTTPS/8443
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Auth OK
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth OK
    Gateway->>MaaSAPI: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+
    MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: Store hashed API key<br/>5432/TCP TLS Password
    PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Key stored
    MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: 201 Created (key metadata)
    Gateway-->>Client: API key response

    Note over Client,PostgreSQL: Flow 3: MaaSModelRef Reconciliation (Controller)

    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    activate K8sAPI
    Note right of K8sAPI: maas-controller watches<br/>MaaSModelRef, LLMInferenceService,<br/>HTTPRoute CRDs via informers
    K8sAPI-->>K8sAPI: MaaSModelRef event
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Validate HTTPRoute exists<br/>Check gateway association
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Read Gateway for endpoint URL
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Update MaaSModelRef status<br/>(phase, endpoint, HTTPRoute)
    deactivate K8sAPI
